attributes.Report_1: Dilling a second well on the field, currently producing 1,600BOPD. Completed installation of a modular Gas processing plant. Wants to start a liquefied petroleum Gas(LPG) market in the host community through a cooperative society acting as offtaker.

Currently producing about 2,200BOPD.Plans a 48km gas pipeline to seplat operated Oben field gas facility, for domestic gas utilisation. Platformform has moved from as high as 1,800BOPD to as low as 600BOPD.
Drilled a dry hole looking for Oil. Th field have more potential as gas pools. P+P is estimated tobe 160 billion cubic feet of gas.
Commenced production 2008. Produces Over 8000 BOPD. Most sustained steady production of all operators.

Finalising the laying of flowlines to the just Umusati - 2 well. Was the 3rd company in the marginal field class of 2004 to reach first Oil, but it has struggled at far below 1,000BOPD and the re-entered well, Umusati-1 died at some point.
Well work over done by AFREN. Low API  assured . not looking good

Walter Smith had a blow out on the rig: the entire rig went up in flames. The company is takling the challenges. it iscurrently drilling a relief well to keep the reservoir fluid pressure in checks. There has been at least three side tracks.
A new local E&P company, Located in SHELL operated mining Lease (OML 17), The Beny Steinmetz Group is technical partner, FOA and FIA are epected to be signed

Hardy oil, technical partner, Millenium oil & Gas, now has an Australian Bank as partner. Hardy had earlier brought in Emerald Resources for Funding purposes. In Oza 4 at flow rates averaging approximately 600stbd and average GOR of 5,466 scf/stb
Talks with Oilflow Group for technical partnership have broken down
Prime Energy raised money finally re-entered and tested Assaramoturu1 well
A new technical E&P Company, awarded Otakikpo field in SHELL (OML 11). The Beny Steinmetz group is the tecchnical partner. FOA and FIA are expected to be signed.

Goland was one of the first members of the marginal field class of 2004 to go on well site, but community disturbances held the company back from drilling, since 2006, leading to severance of relations with partner Vitrioil.
Oando, the technical and financial partner, has ordered equipment (for a 16km pipeline and Jacket), there is progress towards first oil.
Production facility under repair. Downtown has lasted more than four months.
Slow progress, After Afren pulled, there have been several "suitors" but talks recently broke down between Bicta Energy and Ofserv, the Houston Based firm.
Change in design of the entire production  system has slowed down delivery of first hydrocarbon from this field. Seven energythe 62% owner of Universal energy Sinopec is the technical partner
Technical partner, Mart Resources Pulled out after reporting dire finances, there was lack of success with the new well.Qua Iboe 3. Network E&P is looking for new partner

Frontier Oil is awaiting the rig NRG 201 to re-enter, test and complete Uquo-4, the company is in advnced stage of installing equipmen for the hundred million standardcubic feet per day of Gas in Eket.

On sight preparation for most of 2009, trying to convert a swamp location into land and move in a rig. Its partner, Mart resources, was suffering from severe cash crunch at the time. the two companies since parted ways.
